gov.nih.nlm.ling.sem

Class Conjunction

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.nih.nlm.ling.sem.AbstractRelation
      • gov.nih.nlm.ling.sem.Predication
        • gov.nih.nlm.ling.sem.Conjunction
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    HasPredicate, Relation, SemanticItem, java.lang.Comparable<SemanticItem>

    public class Conjunction
extends Predication
    Represents a multiplicity of semantic items.

    No assumption is made regarding the identity of the semantic items, it is not assumed that they are even of the same class. Currently, we assume that there is an explicit predicate that indicates the conjunction, and therefore it extends Predication.

    Author:
    Halil Kilicoglu
